00:28:23,225 --> 00:28:27,490
Sitting ducks. We set up three
snipers and that's all it takes.

254
00:28:28,897 --> 00:28:31,422
- Pay the man.
- All right.

255
00:28:31,599 --> 00:28:32,827
Thank you.

256
00:28:33,034 --> 00:28:35,127
- You didn't count it.
- That's all right.

257
00:28:35,336 --> 00:28:37,327
You should really count it, you know.

258
00:28:37,539 --> 00:28:38,870
It's okay.

259
00:28:39,073 --> 00:28:42,099
Give him something
to help him with his conscience.

260
00:28:45,346 --> 00:28:47,678
No, that's all right. I don't really want it.

261
00:28:47,882 --> 00:28:50,180
Come on, Duffy. I know you need it.

262
00:29:09,470 --> 00:29:11,563
Isn't this a school day?

263
00:29:16,710 --> 00:29:18,337
Cops!

264
00:29:21,081 --> 00:29:22,605
Oh, shit!

265
00:29:30,824 --> 00:29:31,813
Oh, no.

266
00:29:50,376 --> 00:29:51,843
Freeze!

267
00:29:52,578 --> 00:29:55,103
Turn around. Put your hands up.

268
00:30:10,763 --> 00:30:11,752
Shit.

269
00:30:26,144 --> 00:30:28,840
Officer Duffy, have a seat.

270
00:30:35,153 --> 00:30:37,781
You look a little out of breath, bitch.

271
00:30:40,725 --> 00:30:45,685
- You sold us out, Officer Duffy.
- What are you talking about, Murph?

272
00:30:45,864 --> 00:30:48,560
Where is Cain?

273
00:30:48,733 --> 00:30:51,395
I don't know any Cain.

274
00:30:53,538 --> 00:30:55,631
Where is Cain?

275
00:30:55,840 --> 00:30:58,172
I don't know.

276
00:31:05,250 --> 00:31:07,615
Where is Cain?!

277
00:31:07,818 --> 00:31:10,252
I told you, I don't know!

278
00:31:33,811 --> 00:31:35,802
Where?

279
00:31:35,980 --> 00:31:38,505
River Rouge. The old sludge plant.

280
00:31:39,817 --> 00:31:42,081
You're a rotten cop.

281
00:34:34,386 --> 00:34:35,853
Go.

282
00:35:47,558 --> 00:35:50,287
- You.
- You want me?

283
00:35:50,493 --> 00:35:52,120
Dead or alive.

284
00:35:54,097 --> 00:35:55,359
Then one of us must die.

285
00:35:56,266 --> 00:35:57,824
Dead, then.

286
00:36:21,658 --> 00:36:23,421
Jesus...

287
00:36:23,593 --> 00:36:25,652
...had days like this.

288
00:36:26,897 --> 00:36:29,559
Hounded and attacked like a criminal.

289
00:36:30,032 --> 00:36:32,967
But like him, I don't blame you.

290
00:36:33,168 --> 00:36:35,728
They program you, and you do it.

291
00:36:36,405 --> 00:36:41,104
- I will kill you.
- Oh, you just tried.

292
00:36:42,511 --> 00:36:44,001
And...

293
00:36:44,179 --> 00:36:45,476
...I forgive you.

294
00:37:58,185 --> 00:38:00,050
Why'd you stop? You got it cracked.

295
00:38:00,220 --> 00:38:01,448
I'm tired.

296
00:38:01,989 --> 00:38:04,423
They say he's got a brain.
I want to see it.

297
00:38:10,263 --> 00:38:12,754
You think it was me that beat you?

298
00:38:13,066 --> 00:38:14,897
It wasn't.

299
00:38:15,502 --> 00:38:16,799
It was this.

300
00:38:33,119 --> 00:38:34,916
It's too tough.

301
00:38:35,388 --> 00:38:37,515
Try here at the joint.

302
00:38:43,462 --> 00:38:44,690
Yeah!

303
00:38:49,168 --> 00:38:50,795
Look at that!

304
00:39:00,446 --> 00:39:02,539
Come on. Cut it out.

305
00:39:05,418 --> 00:39:07,443
How's it taste?

306
00:39:19,798 --> 00:39:21,231
What the hell's going on?!

307
00:39:22,300 --> 00:39:24,291
Man, just look at him.

308
00:39:26,371 --> 00:39:28,236
Christ, he's been stripped.

309
00:39:41,152 --> 00:39:44,952
Let's not get carried away here.
We're talking about a piece of equipment.

310
00:39:45,156 --> 00:39:47,386
Don't tell me he can't suffer.

311
00:39:47,959 --> 00:39:49,654
Just look at him.

312
00:39:50,161 --> 00:39:52,390
It's electrical.

313
00:39:52,596 --> 00:39:54,257
Bullshit.

314
00:39:54,631 --> 00:39:57,395
I know every inch of him.
Every circuit.

315
00:39:57,601 --> 00:39:59,535
Every living nerve.

316
00:39:59,736 --> 00:40:03,672
His pain centers are alive.
They're lit up like Christmas trees.

317
00:40:03,874 --> 00:40:06,741
The back-up generator's
just making him twitch.

318
00:40:06,944 --> 00:40:08,434
He's suffering.

319
00:40:09,179 --> 00:40:10,510
How long can he last?

320
00:40:10,714 --> 00:40:12,375
No way of knowing.

321
00:40:12,883 --> 00:40:15,215
Got him on minimal life support.

322
00:40:16,386 --> 00:40:19,446
Keeping the brain going
with microshocks.

323
00:40:20,924 --> 00:40:25,293
- It's damn tricky. He could go anytime.
- Move. Move!

324
00:40:26,964 --> 00:40:28,363
What's happening in here?

325
00:40:28,565 --> 00:40:33,024
OCP is happening. These bastards
won't lift a finger to help him.

326
00:40:33,236 --> 00:40:36,103
This unit needs
millions of dollars in parts.

327
00:40:36,272 --> 00:40:40,265
You can't expect authorization for that
kind of cash overnight. Be reasonable.

328
00:40:40,476 --> 00:40:42,205
If you don't fix him, it's murder.

329
00:40:42,411 --> 00:40:45,209
Settle down. I'm doing you
a favor by talking to you.

330
00:40:45,815 --> 00:40:48,978
You son of a bitch. He's in hell.

331
00:40:52,288 --> 00:40:53,653
Fix him!

332
00:40:55,091 --> 00:40:56,649
We'll be in touch.

333
00:41:04,601 --> 00:41:06,967
Oh, man, you guys are the greatest!

334
00:41:07,170 --> 00:41:09,104
Did you see their faces?

335
00:41:09,305 --> 00:41:12,399
"We're gonna throw away
the key, Duffy. "

336
00:41:14,343 --> 00:41:16,641
The cops didn't give you trouble,
did they?

337
00:41:16,812 --> 00:41:20,543
The usual shit from Reed.
They'll never prove anything.

338
00:41:21,049 --> 00:41:22,311
Hey, want some?

339
00:41:22,517 --> 00:41:25,884
Hey, I'm a minor.
Don't want to break any laws.

340
00:41:26,955 --> 00:41:28,479
Here, you take it.

341
00:41:28,690 --> 00:41:30,954
God, I just love you guys!

342
00:41:35,664 --> 00:41:37,154
What happened?

343
00:41:37,966 --> 00:41:39,399
Hey, where we going?

344
00:41:40,068 --> 00:41:43,094
Hey, come on, guys.
This isn't funny, man.

345
00:41:43,305 --> 00:41:45,000
Oh, God, my head.

346
00:41:45,374 --> 00:41:48,343
My head is killing me.

347
00:41:49,544 --> 00:41:51,341
Hey, man. What's...?

348
00:41:51,513 --> 00:41:54,970
Hey, Cain! Hey, it's good to see you.

349
00:41:55,182 --> 00:41:56,740
Thanks for getting me out.

350
00:41:58,486 --> 00:42:00,886
- I can't get up.
- You noticed that one.

351
00:42:01,055 --> 00:42:04,582
- Cain, I don't know what the kid told you...
- You told them, Duffy.

352
00:42:04,759 --> 00:42:07,091
- You told them where we were.
- That's not true.

353
00:42:07,261 --> 00:42:12,028
- We know all about it, Duffy.
- You think you're the only cop we have?

354
00:42:14,669 --> 00:42:16,261
Oh, shit!

355
00:42:16,771 --> 00:42:19,103
Cain. Cain, come on.
Man, I'm begging you, man!

356
00:42:19,273 --> 00:42:21,605
Look, I'll do anything!

357
00:42:21,976 --> 00:42:24,774
Okay. You're kidding, right?
Yeah, you're just kidding.

358
00:42:25,212 --> 00:42:29,046
You scared me.
You taught me a lesson, man.

359
00:42:29,250 --> 00:42:32,447
I'd never fuck with you,
because I really love you guys.

360
00:42:32,620 --> 00:42:34,610
- I really do!
- Shut up!

361
00:42:34,821 --> 00:42:39,087
I've been loyal. I know shit
that I still haven't even told you, Cain!

362
00:42:40,660 --> 00:42:43,595
You deserve this, Duffy.
Cain might have been killed.

363
00:42:43,763 --> 00:42:45,094
Okay. Okay.

364
00:42:45,365 --> 00:42:47,959
Maybe you ought to have the kid leave.

365
00:42:48,835 --> 00:42:52,430
- Why?
- What do you mean, "have the kid leave"?

366
00:42:53,239 --> 00:42:57,266
That's a good touch. That's a good touch.
"Have the kid leave. "

367
00:42:59,312 --> 00:43:01,940
That's good. "Have the kid leave. " Why?

368
00:43:03,550 --> 00:43:06,178
Come on. It's over.

369
00:43:06,553 --> 00:43:09,784
Come on, Cain! Come on, man.
What are you doing?

370
00:43:11,458 --> 00:43:12,982
Come on!

371
00:43:27,873 --> 00:43:30,637
You said you were
just gonna scare him!

372
00:43:30,843 --> 00:43:32,811
Doesn't he look scared?

373
00:43:43,489 --> 00:43:45,286
I can't believe you'd do this.

374
00:43:45,491 --> 00:43:48,426
It hardly matters what you believe,
Mr. Schenk.

375
00:43:48,627 --> 00:43:51,391
But these are criminals.
They're maniacs.

376
00:43:51,597 --> 00:43:54,623
You're giving premature
value judgments.

377
00:43:55,967 --> 00:43:59,403
All right, it may be true.
The subjects are socially misaligned.

378
00:43:59,604 --> 00:44:02,539
Socially misaligned?
These are death row inmates!

379
00:44:02,707 --> 00:44:06,302
And of no use to society. We need a
subject who'll welcome the power...

380
00:44:06,477 --> 00:44:08,342
...the virtual immortality we offer.

381
00:44:08,546 --> 00:44:12,312
Now, I really think this is a good place
to start looking.

382
00:44:13,985 --> 00:44:18,081
- You're out of your mind.
- Is that your professional opinion?

383
00:44:18,756 --> 00:44:21,156
Yes, goddamn it, it is! Yes!

384
00:44:21,359 --> 00:44:25,728
And you are not using my lab to put
that kind of a brain into my cyborg.

385
00:44:25,897 --> 00:44:27,762
We'd dearly miss you here.

386
00:44:29,934 --> 00:44:32,334
You're the one that's gonna be
out of a job.

387
00:44:33,204 --> 00:44:35,865
I'm going to take this directly
to Johnson.

388
00:44:37,073 --> 00:44:40,702
He's just been waiting for an excuse
to get you fired.

389
00:44:48,952 --> 00:44:50,249
Good morning, sir.

390
00:44:51,521 --> 00:44:53,785
I'm sorry to bother you this early.

391
00:44:55,358 --> 00:44:56,689
You seem agitated.

392
00:44:56,893 --> 00:44:59,088
Frankly, I'm shocked.

393
00:44:59,596 --> 00:45:01,188
Mr. Schenk just called.

394
00:45:01,364 --> 00:45:04,993
Dr. Faxx has begun screening
candidates for the Robocop 2 project...

395
00:45:05,202 --> 00:45:08,865
So I understand. It's very exciting.

396
00:45:09,105 --> 00:45:12,040
She's screening psychotics, sir.
Murderers.

397
00:45:12,242 --> 00:45:15,109
We aren't planning to build a toy,
Johnson.

398
00:45:15,278 --> 00:45:16,710
Faxx knows what she's doing.

399
00:45:16,912 --> 00:45:20,643
She's keeping Robocop offline.
It's a public-relations disaster.

400
00:45:21,217 --> 00:45:24,709
You've got to learn to look
at the larger picture. The foreclosure.

401
00:45:24,887 --> 00:45:26,980
You must know how important
that is to us.

402
00:45:27,156 --> 00:45:30,990
With Robocop out of commission, the
chaos down there will increase...

403
00:45:31,227 --> 00:45:33,889
...and the odds the city will fall
into our hands.

404
00:45:34,063 --> 00:45:38,659
But a competent executive would find a way
to deal with the corporate image problem.

405
00:45:38,868 --> 00:45:41,428
Couldn't agree with you more,
Mr. Johnson.

406
00:45:42,671 --> 00:45:44,639
Fortunately, I have found a way.

407
00:45:44,840 --> 00:45:48,332
Yes, Ms. Faxx and I have
already discussed it.

408
00:45:49,578 --> 00:45:53,207
I know you'll help
to implement her ideas.

409
00:45:53,582 --> 00:45:55,277
Of course, sir. Whatever I can do.

410
00:45:55,451 --> 00:45:56,678
Anything else?

411
00:45:57,151 --> 00:45:59,949
- Coffee?
- No, thank you.

412
00:46:00,188 --> 00:46:02,816
Don't forget your shoes
on the way out.

413
00:46:35,957 --> 00:46:38,481
He's my patient and critical.
I must stay with him.

414
00:46:38,659 --> 00:46:40,490
We'll let you know when we need you.

415
00:46:40,661 --> 00:46:43,721
Nobody on your staff has my experience
with him. You need me.

416
00:46:43,931 --> 00:46:45,398
We don't need anybody.

417
00:46:45,599 --> 00:46:48,830
"We. " Who the hell are "we"?
You're a lawyer who knows nothing!

418
00:46:49,036 --> 00:46:51,732
You're exactly this far
from getting fired, babe.

419
00:46:52,406 --> 00:46:54,135
Shyster!

420
00:46:55,309 --> 00:46:56,970
He's one of mine.

421
00:46:57,678 --> 00:46:59,646
I want him back on his feet.

422
00:47:00,247 --> 00:47:03,478
Maybe he will be,
or maybe we'll just sell the parts for scrap.

423
00:47:03,684 --> 00:47:05,345
That's up to us.

424
00:47:05,519 --> 00:47:07,885
You see, Robocop's off warranty.

425
00:47:11,692 --> 00:47:13,284
Robocop's command program...

426
00:47:13,493 --> 00:47:16,860
...his set of directives...

427
00:47:17,064 --> 00:47:21,295
It determines his behavior.
It's time to update the program...

428
00:47:21,500 --> 00:47:25,163
...and I would like to hear
from each one of you.

429
00:47:26,572 --> 00:47:28,506
It's about time they asked us.

430
00:47:28,708 --> 00:47:31,734
We're getting a lot of heat
from parents' groups.

431
00:47:31,911 --> 00:47:34,175
Personally, I don't blame them.
I'm a parent.

432
00:47:34,680 --> 00:47:36,443
All that destructive behavior.

433
00:47:37,049 --> 00:47:39,643
He's become a role model
for our children.

434
00:47:39,852 --> 00:47:42,412
- Now, what are we teaching them?
- You have a point.

435
00:47:42,622 --> 00:47:45,853
If he talked things out with people
instead of firing that gun.

436
00:47:46,559 --> 00:47:49,858
Couldn't he take a little time
to address environmental issues?

437
00:47:50,029 --> 00:47:51,087
What was that?

438
00:47:51,263 --> 00:47:53,629
He could speak out
on environmental issues.

439
00:47:53,833 --> 00:47:55,323
Don't see any reason why not.

440
00:47:55,534 --> 00:47:57,092
For all the shooting he does...

441
00:47:57,269 --> 00:48:00,533
...I've never once seen him take the time
to do anything nice...

442
00:48:01,306 --> 00:48:05,106
...like visit an orphanage.
- You're absolutely right.

443
00:48:05,310 --> 00:48:06,834
Or help a cat out of a tree...

444
00:48:07,012 --> 00:48:09,674
...or go door to door collecting
for the Red Cross...

445
00:48:09,881 --> 00:48:14,545
...or maybe even roasting some
marshmallows with some Cub Scouts.

446
00:48:14,753 --> 00:48:20,055
Why, Mr. Johnson, that is wonderful.
Thank you so much.

447
00:48:25,447 --> 00:48:28,473
- It's no good. The program isn't uploading.
- He's resisting.

448
00:48:28,651 --> 00:48:29,879
There's too much data.

449
00:48:30,052 --> 00:48:34,216
- No, it's him. Leave him to me, Schenk.
- I can't... It's not going to work!

450
00:48:35,691 --> 00:48:37,352
You're wasting valuable time.

451
00:48:37,760 --> 00:48:40,387
- Don't resist us.
- Let me up.

452
00:48:41,095 --> 00:48:42,858
I must go.

453
00:48:44,732 --> 00:48:46,029
Go where?

454
00:48:47,168 --> 00:48:51,764
Do what? Go dancing? Fall in love?
What is it you think you are?

455
00:48:52,340 --> 00:48:54,001
Alex Murphy.

456
00:48:55,643 --> 00:48:56,974
That's a delusion.

457
00:48:57,445 --> 00:49:01,176
It's a glitch in your system.
Alex Murphy is dead.

458
00:49:01,382 --> 00:49:04,909
Take away the metal and wires,
you're just a couple chunks on a table.

459
00:49:05,119 --> 00:49:07,178
You're not even a corpse.

460
00:49:09,657 --> 00:49:10,954
What are you?

461
00:49:13,494 --> 00:49:14,825
Respond.

462
00:49:15,964 --> 00:49:19,490
I am Officer Alex Murphy...

463
00:49:19,700 --> 00:49:21,258
...Detroit Police Department.

464
00:49:21,468 --> 00:49:22,935
That won't do.

465
00:49:30,077 --> 00:49:31,738
What are you?

466
00:49:34,248 --> 00:49:38,082
Robocop. Crime Prevention Unit.

467
00:49:38,518 --> 00:49:39,917
OCP.

468
00:49:40,487 --> 00:49:42,751
Better. Much better.

469
00:49:46,660 --> 00:49:47,922
I type it. You think it.

470
00:49:48,829 --> 00:49:51,491
You type it. I think it.

471
00:49:52,099 --> 00:49:54,932
What a wonderful opportunity
you represent.

472
00:49:55,502 --> 00:49:57,868
Psychotherapy, it's such a...

473
00:49:58,772 --> 00:50:03,231
It's a slow, clumsy practice.
But with you this is so simple.

474
00:50:03,442 --> 00:50:05,137
Direct.

475
00:50:12,418 --> 00:50:13,680
You're lucky.

476
00:50:13,886 --> 00:50:17,754
We can do in moments with you what
would take years with a human patient.

477
00:50:18,924 --> 00:50:21,188
I'm really very lucky.

478
00:50:21,394 --> 00:50:25,626
You're free. You're free from doubt.
Free from having to make painful choices.

479
00:50:27,867 --> 00:50:29,494
I am free.

480
00:50:30,536 --> 00:50:32,163
He's ready.

481
00:50:33,572 --> 00:50:35,369
Uploading command program.

482
00:50:38,878 --> 00:50:42,074
I am so glad we had this chance
to dialogue.

483
00:50:53,591 --> 00:50:56,116
Look at you. It's like you're brand-new.

484
00:50:56,328 --> 00:50:57,693
Thank you. Thank you.

485
00:50:57,862 --> 00:50:59,921
You really had us worried there, Murphy.

486
00:51:00,098 --> 00:51:01,429
I'm touched.

487
00:51:01,633 --> 00:51:03,328
Get this guy.

488
00:51:04,135 --> 00:51:05,568
He's touched.

489
00:51:06,571 --> 00:51:10,564
That's enough. All of you,
back to your posts. Come on. Let's go.

490
00:51:14,346 --> 00:51:15,779
How you feeling, Murphy?

491
00:51:15,980 --> 00:51:19,507
I'm just fine, Warren.
Thank you for asking.

492
00:51:20,318 --> 00:51:21,875
Let's get you downstairs.

493
00:51:22,086 --> 00:51:25,453
I want to see what those amateurs
at OCP screwed up.

494
00:51:25,723 --> 00:51:29,022
Pity. It's a beautiful morning.

495
00:51:29,693 --> 00:51:31,285
Shame to waste it.

496
00:51:33,297 --> 00:51:35,458
- Ready for duty, partner?
- You betcha.

497
00:51:35,666 --> 00:51:38,157
- Let's go.
- Nothing I'd rather do.

498
00:51:40,304 --> 00:51:41,931
He sounds terrific.

499
00:51:42,139 --> 00:51:43,663
Something's wrong.

500
00:52:11,200 --> 00:52:12,258
Harder!

501
00:52:25,047 --> 00:52:27,914
It's Robo!
Everybody out the back door!

502
00:52:30,420 --> 00:52:32,547
- It's locked!
- It won't open!

503
00:52:37,193 --> 00:52:39,161
Murph, wake up, will you?

504
00:52:47,269 --> 00:52:49,032
Good morning.

505
00:52:54,176 --> 00:52:56,144
Come on, take him out.

506
