01:20:08,896 --> 01:20:11,228
It's business we're talking about here.

764
01:20:11,432 --> 01:20:13,764
Do you have any idea
how many people we employ?

765
01:20:13,968 --> 01:20:17,335
No. I never thought
about it like that.

766
01:20:17,505 --> 01:20:18,631
Sharp kid.

767
01:20:19,007 --> 01:20:20,235
So...

768
01:20:20,908 --> 01:20:22,431
...your war on crime...

769
01:20:22,643 --> 01:20:24,304
...you want to win it or what?

770
01:20:25,212 --> 01:20:27,737
We're the only chance you have.

771
01:20:27,948 --> 01:20:29,711
Listen to him.

772
01:20:29,916 --> 01:20:31,645
He's got it all worked out.

773
01:20:38,425 --> 01:20:39,824
Why do people do crimes?

774
01:20:41,194 --> 01:20:44,960
- Why? Drugs. People do drugs.
- Because they want drugs.

775
01:20:45,165 --> 01:20:47,497
The kind that cost too much.

776
01:20:48,201 --> 01:20:51,034
Nuke gives high quality
at a cheap price.

777
01:20:51,238 --> 01:20:53,536
If you get off our backs,
we'll make it cheaper.

778
01:20:53,740 --> 01:20:54,729
And safer.

779
01:20:54,941 --> 01:20:57,307
We don't shove our shit
down anybody's throat.

780
01:20:57,511 --> 01:21:01,072
And we don't advertise it
like they do with cigarettes or booze.

781
01:21:01,281 --> 01:21:03,111
So leave us alone...

782
01:21:03,315 --> 01:21:06,113
...and anybody who wants it gets it.

783
01:21:08,721 --> 01:21:10,279
So no more crimes.

784
01:21:10,623 --> 01:21:14,184
You get to be the mayor
who cleaned up Detroit.

785
01:21:21,701 --> 01:21:23,498
He's got a point.

786
01:21:24,704 --> 01:21:26,365
Don't you think he's got a point?

787
01:21:26,572 --> 01:21:28,540
Yeah, he's got a point.

788
01:21:34,080 --> 01:21:35,513
What the hell is that?

789
01:21:45,090 --> 01:21:46,785
Get out!

790
01:22:51,889 --> 01:22:53,823
Marv, are...?

791
01:24:33,721 --> 01:24:35,382
Cain.

792
01:24:35,990 --> 01:24:37,423
Oh, wow.

793
01:24:41,262 --> 01:24:43,059
You look great.

794
01:25:41,654 --> 01:25:44,521
It'll take some getting used to...

795
01:25:46,925 --> 01:25:49,450
...but it'll be great, Cain.

796
01:28:51,305 --> 01:28:52,533
Lie still.

797
01:28:58,045 --> 01:29:01,640
- I'm cold.
- You are going into shock.

798
01:29:02,116 --> 01:29:04,744
I will call for a medical emergency unit.

799
01:29:05,052 --> 01:29:07,316
Wait. No.

800
01:29:09,156 --> 01:29:10,919
Don't leave me.

801
01:29:13,727 --> 01:29:15,718
I won't leave you.

802
01:29:20,867 --> 01:29:22,630
Who did this?

803
01:29:22,836 --> 01:29:24,599
It was big.

804
01:29:25,238 --> 01:29:27,536
Bigger than you.

805
01:29:28,108 --> 01:29:29,803
It was Cain.

806
01:29:31,645 --> 01:29:33,613
I'm gonna die.

807
01:29:36,049 --> 01:29:38,540
You know what that's like, don't you?

808
01:29:39,719 --> 01:29:42,210
It really sucks.

809
01:29:48,528 --> 01:29:50,051
Yes.

810
01:30:10,916 --> 01:30:14,977
<i>Thirteen dead in what appears
to be a Nuke money massacre.</i>

811
01:30:15,187 --> 01:30:18,247
<i>Among the victims,
two city councilmen.</i>

812
01:30:18,457 --> 01:30:21,620
<i>Was the city trying to strike a deal
with the drug lords?</i>

813
01:30:21,827 --> 01:30:24,887
No comment!
I said, I have no comment!

814
01:30:25,097 --> 01:30:27,031
No comments on these allegations.

815
01:30:27,233 --> 01:30:30,224
These were men
who served this city tirelessly.

816
01:30:30,435 --> 01:30:34,633
However, I make a promise
to the people of Detroit City...

817
01:30:34,839 --> 01:30:38,036
...that no effort will be spared
to investigate this thoroughly!

818
01:30:38,243 --> 01:30:40,040
But, Mr. Mayor, what about...?

819
01:30:40,245 --> 01:30:42,736
I'm sorry. No more questions.

820
01:30:42,947 --> 01:30:44,972
<i>Our own Mayor Kuzak.</i>

821
01:30:45,183 --> 01:30:46,844
<i>Now let's go live to Jess.</i>

822
01:30:47,051 --> 01:30:52,079
And here it is, the Civic Centrum, OCP's
100-story gift to the Motor City.

823
01:30:52,257 --> 01:30:55,283
While debate continues
over OCP's hostile takeover...

824
01:30:55,460 --> 01:30:58,054
...there's no denying
the mood down here is festive.

825
01:30:58,229 --> 01:31:01,721
Citizens interviewed on the scene
expressed excitement and hope...

826
01:31:01,933 --> 01:31:06,097
...that OCP will make good on its
promise of a better life in Detroit.

827
01:31:06,304 --> 01:31:08,329
- Press!
- Sorry, folks, media only.

828
01:31:08,506 --> 01:31:10,700
TV and press only.
You'll have to step back.

829
01:31:19,483 --> 01:31:20,711
There he is!

830
01:31:27,190 --> 01:31:29,317
Can OCP bring industry
back to Detroit?

831
01:31:29,526 --> 01:31:32,086
Does OCP own the city?
Will you hold elections?

832
01:31:32,296 --> 01:31:35,561
- Do we become OCP employees?
- Why not go to City Hall?

833
01:31:35,766 --> 01:31:37,256
Just a minute.

834
01:31:37,801 --> 01:31:39,666
I'll answer that, young lady.

835
01:31:39,870 --> 01:31:44,466
City Hall is the decaying symbol
of mismanagement and corruption.

836
01:31:44,641 --> 01:31:45,869
You get that?

837
01:31:46,043 --> 01:31:49,979
This magnificent structure will be the seat
of leadership for the new Detroit.

838
01:31:50,147 --> 01:31:53,411
And what better place
for a clean, fresh start?

839
01:31:53,616 --> 01:31:56,642
And so, people of the press...

840
01:31:56,852 --> 01:31:58,547
...city officials...

841
01:31:58,754 --> 01:32:01,951
...in a few minutes
Omni Consumer Products...

842
01:32:02,158 --> 01:32:04,922
...and the troubled city of Detroit...

843
01:32:05,127 --> 01:32:08,927
...will join in a bold new venture.

844
01:32:09,131 --> 01:32:11,122
Now I'd like to explain...

845
01:32:11,334 --> 01:32:13,199
...just what this will mean.

846
01:32:13,402 --> 01:32:16,064
Sometimes we just
have to start over...

847
01:32:16,272 --> 01:32:17,603
...from scratch...

848
01:32:17,807 --> 01:32:19,638
...to make things right.

849
01:32:20,109 --> 01:32:23,476
And that's exactly
what we're going to do.

850
01:32:23,779 --> 01:32:26,247
We're going to build
a brand-new city...

851
01:32:26,449 --> 01:32:28,713
...where Detroit now stands.

852
01:32:28,918 --> 01:32:30,852
An example...

853
01:32:31,053 --> 01:32:32,679
...to the world.

854
01:32:53,641 --> 01:32:54,869
My friends...

855
01:32:55,043 --> 01:32:58,274
...welcome to our city
as it should be.

856
01:32:58,513 --> 01:33:02,347
And as it will be,
in the hands of responsible...

857
01:33:02,550 --> 01:33:04,745
...private enterprise.

858
01:33:05,920 --> 01:33:07,911
And a special welcome...

859
01:33:08,123 --> 01:33:11,456
...to Mayor Kuzak
and the outgoing administration.

860
01:33:11,659 --> 01:33:13,558
We're not going anywhere.

861
01:33:14,261 --> 01:33:15,558
Your Honor.

862
01:33:17,931 --> 01:33:21,025
You'll have to tear down a lot
of houses to make that.

863
01:33:21,235 --> 01:33:22,964
I mean, take away their homes!

864
01:33:23,170 --> 01:33:26,196
We're going to raise towers
of glass and steel.

865
01:33:26,407 --> 01:33:30,173
Every citizen will have a living unit,
safe, secure, and clean.

866
01:33:30,377 --> 01:33:31,844
Now, please take your seat.

867
01:33:32,045 --> 01:33:34,172
Won't be much room for neighborhoods.

868
01:33:34,381 --> 01:33:36,542
Not like the kind we all grew up in.

869
01:33:36,750 --> 01:33:39,742
Today neighborhoods are places
where bad things happen.

870
01:33:39,920 --> 01:33:41,148
Don't be nostalgic.

871
01:33:41,355 --> 01:33:44,415
What about democracy?
Nobody elected you.

872
01:33:44,625 --> 01:33:46,991
Anyone can buy OCP stock...

873
01:33:47,194 --> 01:33:49,754
...and own a piece of our city.

874
01:33:50,731 --> 01:33:52,960
What could be more democratic
than that?

875
01:33:53,166 --> 01:33:57,626
There's a lot of people in this town
that can't afford to buy your stock!

876
01:33:57,837 --> 01:33:59,998
And they won't let you
get away with this.

877
01:34:00,406 --> 01:34:02,374
You haven't been following the polls.

878
01:34:04,143 --> 01:34:05,701
Sit down.

879
01:34:06,946 --> 01:34:09,881
Sit down, mayor.

880
01:34:13,352 --> 01:34:15,946
About a year ago
we gave this city Robocop.

881
01:34:16,155 --> 01:34:18,453
I think he's worked out pretty well.

882
01:34:18,658 --> 01:34:20,956
But things have become
rougher out there.

883
01:34:21,160 --> 01:34:24,095
And now we need
a law enforcement unit...

884
01:34:24,297 --> 01:34:26,561
...able to meet the enemy
on his own ground...

885
01:34:26,766 --> 01:34:29,564
...and carrying enough firepower...

886
01:34:29,769 --> 01:34:32,169
...to get the job done.

887
01:34:36,908 --> 01:34:38,967
Ladies and gentlemen...

888
01:34:39,177 --> 01:34:40,906
...with great pleasure...

889
01:34:41,246 --> 01:34:42,736
...I give you...

890
01:34:42,948 --> 01:34:45,109
...Robocop 2.

891
01:34:54,159 --> 01:34:57,094
- Those bastards are maniacs!
- What's the matter?

892
01:34:57,295 --> 01:35:00,196
I can't believe it.
It was them! They sent it!

893
01:35:00,398 --> 01:35:01,831
Sent what?

894
01:35:02,367 --> 01:35:03,595
Nothing.

895
01:35:03,768 --> 01:35:06,168
There going to be a big call
for this unit.

896
01:35:06,371 --> 01:35:08,532
And we'll make him right here in Detroit.

897
01:35:08,740 --> 01:35:11,675
That means jobs
we can all be proud of.

898
01:35:11,877 --> 01:35:14,003
And make "Made in America"...

899
01:35:14,211 --> 01:35:16,543
...mean something again.

900
01:35:19,550 --> 01:35:21,609
This single container...

901
01:35:21,819 --> 01:35:24,947
...holds enough Nuke
to addict a city block.

902
01:35:25,456 --> 01:35:28,220
A hundred of these
are produced every day...

903
01:35:28,392 --> 01:35:29,825
...and sent to sweatshops...

904
01:35:30,027 --> 01:35:32,962
...where urban slaves
prepare this poison...

905
01:35:33,163 --> 01:35:36,189
...for our friends, our loved ones,
our children.

906
01:35:36,400 --> 01:35:37,924
Now, I say...

907
01:35:38,135 --> 01:35:41,400
...it's high time
we put an end to this plague.

908
01:35:41,605 --> 01:35:45,701
Robocop 2 will seek out
every laboratory...

909
01:35:45,910 --> 01:35:49,073
...every dealer,
and rid our city of Nuke.

910
01:35:53,350 --> 01:35:54,646
Yes.

911
01:35:54,851 --> 01:35:58,014
Things will be a lot quieter
with this boy around.

912
01:36:13,736 --> 01:36:16,034
- What's wrong with him?
- It's nothing.

913
01:36:16,239 --> 01:36:18,730
- Nothing at all.
- Turn him off.

914
01:36:19,842 --> 01:36:21,070
I can't.

915
01:36:21,277 --> 01:36:23,541
Cain! Let's step outside.

916
01:36:26,316 --> 01:36:29,308
You! Get out of here!
You're obsolete!

917
01:36:29,519 --> 01:36:31,077
That thing is a killer!

918
01:36:31,254 --> 01:36:34,711
- It's not even armed! It's harmless!
- It's a killer, and I saw it!

919
01:36:50,872 --> 01:36:53,306
- Take her out of here! Now!
- Let me go!

920
01:37:14,429 --> 01:37:16,919
Behave yourselves!

921
01:38:04,477 --> 01:38:08,538
- What's the deal here?
- Christ knows. Sounds like a war in there.

922
01:39:22,253 --> 01:39:25,120
You're coming with me, Cain.

923
01:41:23,938 --> 01:41:25,428
There he is!

924
01:41:37,118 --> 01:41:40,645
- All right, get back!
- Are you jealous of the replacement?

925
01:42:31,204 --> 01:42:34,037
This could look bad for OCP, Johnson.

926
01:42:34,641 --> 01:42:37,439
Scramble the best spin team we have.

927
01:43:47,112 --> 01:43:49,580
Ammo! Ammo!

928
01:44:09,733 --> 01:44:11,223
Get down!

929
01:44:32,990 --> 01:44:34,218
Hold your fire!

930
01:44:34,825 --> 01:44:37,385
Hold your fire, damn it!

931
01:44:59,615 --> 01:45:01,048
Let's get him out of here.

932
01:45:03,352 --> 01:45:06,685
Watch his neck. He's hurt bad. Easy.

933
01:45:13,062 --> 01:45:14,290
Shit!

934
01:45:16,032 --> 01:45:17,021
I gotta get back.

935
01:45:17,233 --> 01:45:19,258
Move it back! Move it back!

936
01:45:34,483 --> 01:45:36,883
Let's give him what he wants.

937
01:47:37,135 --> 01:47:38,898
Goodbye.

938
01:48:11,102 --> 01:48:13,434
It's serious trouble.
So many dead and wounded.

939
01:48:13,638 --> 01:48:15,629
There won't be trouble from the dead.

940
01:48:15,840 --> 01:48:18,001
They'll have relatives. They always do.

941
01:48:18,209 --> 01:48:21,178
- It'll be a feeding frenzy.
- It's only money.

942
01:48:21,379 --> 01:48:23,404
- What about criminal proceedings?
- Well...

943
01:48:23,614 --> 01:48:27,448
...we're looking at major indictments, sir.
Prison terms.

944
01:48:27,618 --> 01:48:30,246
- What about me?
- You know we'll do whatever we can.

945
01:48:30,454 --> 01:48:32,285
- That's not good enough.
- Sir?

946
01:48:32,490 --> 01:48:34,754
What if this was the work
of one individual?

947
01:48:34,925 --> 01:48:38,861
A person who had her own agenda, wasn't
in sync with the goals of our company?

948
01:48:39,063 --> 01:48:41,793
Well, that usually works.

949
01:48:42,300 --> 01:48:44,733
A woman who was not a team player.

950
01:48:44,934 --> 01:48:47,528
Who violated our trust.

951
01:48:48,738 --> 01:48:50,968
Easy, easy.

952
01:48:51,474 --> 01:48:52,964
Well...

953
01:48:53,176 --> 01:48:55,610
...we'd need some evidence
to support that.

954
01:48:55,779 --> 01:48:58,543
Sir, whether it exists or not,
I know I can find it.

955
01:48:58,748 --> 01:49:01,740
She did choose the brain, sir.

956
01:49:03,253 --> 01:49:05,483
- Good thinking.
- Sir.

957
01:49:05,689 --> 01:49:07,816
Thank God you're all right.

958
01:49:08,024 --> 01:49:11,323
I was worried. I thought
it was going to hurt you.

959
01:49:11,528 --> 01:49:13,587
It's over. It's all over.

960
01:49:14,964 --> 01:49:16,454
I failed you.

961
01:49:16,666 --> 01:49:20,500
Don't be hard on yourself.
Everything's going to be all right.

962
01:49:23,173 --> 01:49:27,268
Johnson, that business
we were talking about.

963
01:49:27,443 --> 01:49:29,343
Get right on it.

964
01:49:33,549 --> 01:49:35,016
Yes, sir.

965
01:49:39,588 --> 01:49:42,648
Just look at what they've done.
They are criminals.

966
01:49:42,825 --> 01:49:45,589
OCP won't own this city for long.
And I'll see to that.

967
01:49:45,794 --> 01:49:48,160
I'll take it to the streets
and the people.

968
01:49:48,364 --> 01:49:49,729
What has it come to?

969
01:49:49,932 --> 01:49:52,594
Businessmen can buy our rights
like stock?

970
01:49:52,801 --> 01:49:54,860
You don't realize what we're losing!

971
01:49:56,739 --> 01:49:58,934
- Right here, sir!
- Give us a statement!

972
01:49:59,141 --> 01:50:02,838
Dozens are dead.
Is this your idea of a better life?

973
01:50:03,045 --> 01:50:06,878
- Was this an experiment of some kind?
- He was crazy. How did it happen?

974
01:50:07,081 --> 01:50:10,983
- Did you build it to take control?
- How do you account for this disaster?

975
01:50:11,185 --> 01:50:14,348
Will OCP make reparations
to the victims?

976
01:50:15,123 --> 01:50:17,557
That son of a bitch
is getting away with it.

977
01:50:17,759 --> 01:50:19,624
We can't even touch him.

978
01:50:21,129 --> 01:50:22,892
Patience, Lewis.

979
01:50:24,465 --> 01:50:26,365
We're only human.

980
